    <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">CHAPTER 1 - LlamaIndex Architecture (Core Mental Model)</h2>

    <p>→ LlamaIndex is a data orchestration layer between our data and the LLM.<br>
        → It solves <strong>"How do I efficiently retrieve the right context and feed it to an LLM?"</strong></p>

    <h3>The Problem It Solves</h3>
    <h4>Generally Raw LLM has following Limitations:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Have limited context windows</li>
        <li>Cannot search our database/files natively</li>
        <li>Most importantly Hallucinate without grounding (without base knowledge)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>The Core Pipeline of LlamaIndex</h3>
    <pre><code class="language-text">Raw Data → Documents → Nodes → Index → Retriever → Query Engine → LLM → Response</code></pre>
    <br>

    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Layer</th>
                <th>Role</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Data Layer</td>
                <td>Documents / Nodes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Storage Layer</td>
                <td>Index</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Retrieval Layer</td>
                <td>Retriever</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Orchestration Layer</td>
                <td>Query Engine</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Intelligence Layer</td>
                <td>LLM</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>

