    <p><strong>5. Query Engine</strong><br>
        Query Engine is an orchestrator.</p>
    <ol>
        <li>It takes the user query.</li>
        <li>Then Calls retriever.</li>
        <li>Gets relevant nodes.</li>
        <li>Sends those nodes to LLM.</li>
        <li>Synthesizes the response from LLM.</li>
        <li>Returns the final answer to user.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="usage-box">
        <strong>Note:</strong> This is the core step in production based RAG system.
    </div>

    <p><strong>6. LLM</strong><br>
        LLM generates the final answer based on the <strong>user query</strong> and the <strong>retrieved
            context</strong> (aka nodes).<br>
        <em>Note: In this complete learning roadmap, we will be using Gemini as our LLM.</em>
    </p>

